Test Case Examples:
Stream Safety Validation Behavior
The system should validate safety compliance of goods bogies using the allMatch() stream operation and enforce the cargo safety rule.
Cylindrical Bogie Cargo Rule
Cylindrical bogies must carry only Petroleum cargo. If any cylindrical bogie carries a different cargo, the validation must fail.
Valid Train Formation
If all cylindrical bogies carry Petroleum and other bogie types carry any cargo, the train should be marked safe.
Invalid Train Formation
If even one cylindrical bogie carries cargo other than Petroleum, the train should be marked unsafe.
Non-Cylindrical Bogie Flexibility
Bogie types such as Open or Box should allow different cargo types without failing the safety rule.
Empty Dataset Handling
If no goods bogies exist, safety validation should return true, since no rule violations exist.
